The number of CPU clocks necessary to make the 'far' or
full-pointer call by pushing the segment register, the offset,
then issuing a 'lret' is 33 clocks on a Pentium II.
longcall clocks = 46
call clocks = 13
actual full-pointer call clocks = 33
